def calculate_summation_of_absolute_differences(nums):
    n = len(nums)
    result = [0] * n

    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            if i != j:
                result[i] += abs(nums[i] - nums[j])

    return result
```

    The algorithm iterates through each element `nums[i]` in the given integer array `nums`. For each element `nums[i]`, it also iterates through all other elements `nums[j]` in the array, skipping the case when `i == j`. Then, it calculates the absolute difference between `nums[i]` and `nums[j]`, and sums it to the corresponding result for element `nums[i]`. After iterating through all elements, an array `result` containing the summations of absolute differences for each element is returned.

